===Noun===
{{en-noun|slaveries}}

# An [[institution]] or [[social]] [[practice]] of [[own]]ing human beings as [[property]], especially for use as [[forced]] [[laborer]]s.
# A condition of [[servitude]] endured by a [[slave]].
# {{figurative}} A condition in which one is [[captivate]]d or [[subjugate]]d, as by greed or drugs.
#* '''1818''', [[w:Percy_Bysshe_Shelley|Percy Bysshe Shelley]],"The Revolt of Islam", canto 8, stanza 16,
#*: Man seeks for gold in mines that he may weave / A lasting chain for his own '''slavery'''.

